cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with planar graphs and orthogonal drawings, which are common topics in computational geometry.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of the problem and presents algorithms for solving it.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possibility as the paper discusses the problem of finding a common drawing for multiple graphs, which can be seen as a game between the graphs.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possibility as the paper discusses the NP-completeness of the problem.
